Hello, we are seeking some perfs on our project.
I came across this in CCRenderTexture

```c++
        auto dataLen = powW * powH * 4;
        data = malloc(dataLen);
        CC_BREAK_IF(! data);

        memset(data, 0, dataLen);
```

I understand you want the newly RT to be clean ... but as for some reasons it is advised to do a glClear() after a RT is binded (for Tiled Architecture on mobile)... and that the Render Texture is fully rendered into ... and that glTexImage2D() accept null pointers as data ... 

i was wondering if it could become a configurable thing not to allocate and do the memset ?

We tried this option and we had quit a lot of gain .... talking about 10 fps gain for about 40 renders in 40 different RTs , which is what we want.

Maybe there is something I overlooked and you have a good reason to do that ... but I'd like your advise on that point.

Thanks for your work and feed back

